# part2/ssh/authorized_keys.example
# ILLUSTRATIVE / PROPOSED entry for the backup service account's
# ~backup/.ssh/authorized_keys (not a real key).
#
# Mirrors the Part 2 control: restrict the backup key by internal source and
# bind it to a forced command so a stolen key can only run the backup workflow.
#
# Options:
#   from="..."     accept this key only from approved internal sources
#                  (placeholder CIDR/hosts below - replace with the real ones)
#   command="..."  force the backup wrapper; ignore any client-supplied command
#   restrict       disable pty, port/agent/X11 forwarding (enable none by default)
#
# The public key material below is a non-functional placeholder.

from="10.0.0.0/8",command="/usr/local/sbin/backup-wrapper",restrict ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAExampleExampleExampleExamplePLACEHOLDER backup@orchestrator
